This GLSL fragment shader code demonstrates how to manually implement clip plane functionality when using custom shaders in Panda3D, checking each active clip plane against vertex positions to discard fragments outside the viewable area.

void main() {
  if (dot(p3d_ClipPlane[0], vpos) < 0) {
    discard;
  }
  if (dot(p3d_ClipPlane[1], vpos) < 0) {
    discard;
  }

  // Rest of fragment shader
}
